data.title: Palantir stock reaches record high. Govt shutdown may impact Q4 guidance. Impact uncertain.
data.description: Palantir's stock reached a new peak as it surged before the release of its Q3 earnings report. Concerns arise that the ongoing U.S. government shutdown might affect the company's Q4 guidance.

data.title: Western Digital stock hits record highs after earnings, boosted by AI-driven demand. 230% rally in 2021.
data.description: Western Digital's latest earnings report highlighted the growing demand for hard-disk drives powered by artificial intelligence (AI). Following this report, Western Digital's stock reached record highs. The influence of AI has been significant, contributing to a remarkable 230% increase in the company's stock performance this year. This trend demonstrates the increasing reliance on AI-driven technologies in driving growth and innovation within the technology sector.

data.title: Stock of Edwards Lifesciences rose following strong quarterly performance and improved 2025 outlook, driven by 'Halo Effect'.
data.description: The stock of Edwards Lifesciences increased on Friday following the medtech company's announcement of an improved 2025 forecast after surpassing quarterly expectations. This development reflects the positive impact on the company's primary revenue generator.

data.title: Gilead stock reverses with smaller losses; analysts optimistic about new HIV prevention shot.
data.description: On Friday, Gilead stock experienced a turnaround, rising after initial losses due to positive signs regarding its recently approved HIV prevention injection. Analysts highlighted promising factors, leading to the stock's climb. The company's new HIV shot showed potential, despite a miss on the buy side. This update underscores optimism surrounding Gilead's latest medical offering, indicating a potential market impact.

data.title: Church & Dwight Co. (NYSE: CHD) stock rises as Q3 earnings per share of 81 cents beat estimates. Sales hit $1.585 billion (+5% YoY).
data.description: Shares of Church & Dwight Company, Inc. (NYSE: CHD) rose as the company announced third-quarter adjusted earnings per share of 81 cents, surpassing the expected 74 cents. The quarter also saw quarterly sales hit $1.585 billion, marking a 5% increase from the previous year and beating the anticipated $1.536 billion. Organic sales metrics showed a 3.4% rise, attributed to a volume growth of 4% despite a negative pricing and mix impact of 0.6%. CEO Rick Dierker noted, "We continue to drive both dollar and volume share gains across most of our brands."

data.title: Enemærke & Petersen to refurbish 3B Folehaven in Valby with 972 units for DKK 1,033 million in second largest project.
data.description: Enemærke & Petersen, a business unit of MT Højgaard Holding, has secured the main refurbishment and renewal contract for the 3B Folehaven area in Valby, consisting of 972 housing units. The project, valued at DKK 1,033 million, marks the second largest refurbishment assignment in Enemærke & Petersen's history. The formal contract is expected to be finalized after the standstill period ends on November 10, 2025, subject to a schedule B commitment from Landsbyggefonden.

data.title: Apple reported strong Q4 results with record sales in iPhone and Services, analysts bullish with price targets up to $320.
data.description: Apple, Inc. reported a strong fourth-quarter, with record sales in iPhone and Services, showing solid demand. Leading analysts are optimistic about Apple's performance. JPMorgan maintained an Overweight rating, raising Apple's price target to $305. JPMorgan analyst credited iPhone 17 momentum for the better-than-expected results and mentioned growth in Services revenue at 15% year-over-year. Meanwhile, Goldman Sachs maintained a Buy rating, raising Apple's price target to $320. Apple's positive outlook is driven by upcoming launches and new AI features, with Services revenue growth calming regulatory concerns. The full story is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: BofA CEO warns shutdown could slow economy; economist sees rising recession risk as month-long government shutdown begins to damage US economy. Moynihan warns of broader slowdown if standoff continues. Mooney warns longer shutdown will affect more parts of economy.
data.description: Bank of America CEO Brian Moynihan and Moody's Analytics chief economist Mark Zandi have issued warnings about the economic impact of the ongoing government shutdown in the US. Moynihan cautioned that the standoff could slow the economy, leading to a broader "malaise," while Zandi suggested a recession is likely if the impasse continues through the end of the year. Moynihan highlighted that government approvals are crucial for various activities, and delays in areas like the FAA could have ripple effects, impacting business activities. The banking industry is offering support to affected federal workers, but Moynihan emphasized that prolonged shutdown could have a wider economic impact. He urged for a resolution to prevent further damage.

data.title: Otter Tail Power Co. seeks Minnesota rate hike, starting 18-24 month review process with PUC. (Character Count: 104)
data.description: In Fergus Falls, Minnesota, Otter Tail Power Company, a subsidiary of Otter Tail Corporation (Nasdaq: OTTR), has filed a petition with the Minnesota Public Utilities Commission (PUC) to raise electric rates for customers in the state. This request marks the beginning of an extensive 18- to 24-month examination process by the PUC to scrutinize the company’s expenses related to electric service provision, eventually determining fair rates for both the utility and customers.

data.title: Delta Sands plans to build a 3-million-ton-per-year frac sand facility in Buffalo, Texas, meeting demand for in-basin proppant in the Western Haynesville Shale.
data.description: In Buffalo, Texas, Delta Sands LLC revealed its intention to build a new wet sand processing plant with a capacity of 3 million tons annually. This facility will be strategically positioned near Buffalo, Texas, within the Western Haynesville Shale region. The goal behind this project is to address the rising need for premium in-basin proppant due to the rapid growth of natural gas operations and infrastructure in East Texas. The plant is currently in the planning and authorization stages and is expected to generate 40/200 mesh sand.
